{"title":"The new Wilier Adlar adventure bike takes 35kg luggage max load and fits 52mm tyres","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/wilier-adlar-gravel-bike","date":1693497540000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/wilier-adlar-gravel-bike\">The new Wilier Adlar adventure bike takes 35kg luggage max load and fits 52mm tyres</a></p>\n\n<p>The new Wilier Adlar is the Italian brand’s latest <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/what-is-a-gravel-bike\" target=\"_blank\">gravel bike</a>, diving headlong into the growing trend for drop bar bikes with an adventure flair. The Adlar starts from a more MTB-inspired geometry than Wilier’s other gravel bikes, with a longer reach, slacker head tube and steeper seat tube, as well as tyre clearance for 700c x 52mm or 29 x 2”.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame is built around a fork with longer length blades, meaning the Adlar works with a suspension fork too. The rigid fork supplied as standard features dynamo routing, but cables are kept tidy with partial internal routing. Wilier says the 1,100g frame itself has been reinforced to cope with up to 35kg worth of luggage, and a 4-bag <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/buyers-guide-best-bikepacking-bags\" target=\"_blank\">Miss Grape bikepacking kit</a> is available to purchase with the bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Wilier Adlar gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-7-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Alberto Squizzato</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Adlar is available in five different builds, with prices starting from starting from £3,182 for the GRX 11spd-equipped model, rising up to £4,644 for the SRAM Rival XPLR-equipped model with the Miss Grape bikepacking kit.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikepacking-tips\">Tunisia Diaries: 7 things I wish I had known before I set off on my bikepacking adventure</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-gravel-bike\">Best of the best gravel bikes 2023: Cyclist’s top-rated gravel and adventure bikes</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/wilier-rave-slr-gravel-bike\">Wilier Rave SLR: The choose-your-own-adventure gravel road mashup</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Going long</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Wilier Adlar gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-2-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Luca Violetto</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Wilier says the Adlar’s geometry takes inspiration from its mountain bikes, with a slack head tube angle – 70° – and a steep seat tube angle – 74° for a size medium – to keep the rider centred and stable. This is paired with a relatively long 1,065mm wheelbase, and the result is similar to that of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/yt-szepter-review\" target=\"_blank\">YT’s Szepter</a> or <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/bmc-urs-01-review\" target=\"_blank\">BMC’s URS</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While the stack is pretty standard for an adventure gravel bike, at 586mm for a medium, the reach is comparatively long at 413mm. Wilier says this is to allow the use of a shorter stem, which should aid handling when the bike is fully loaded.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What’s in a frame?</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-11-647x970.jpg\" alt=\"Wilier Adlar gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-11-647x970.jpg 647w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-11-200x300.jpg 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-11-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-11-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-11-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-11-750x1124.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-11-1140x1709.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-11-scaled.jpg 1708w\" /><figcaption>Alberto Squizzato</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The Adlar has a competitive claimed frame weight of 1,100g, especially keeping in mind the stated reinforcements for the 35kg max load.<br />Available in five sizes from XS to XL, the Adlar frameset uses a long fork to allow for wider tyre clearance, with claims of 700c x 52mm or 29 x 2” tyre capacity. This also means there is scope for a suspension fork – with a max travel of 40mm – and a dropper post can be fitted as well.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Wilier Adlar gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-9-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Alberto Squizzato</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The fork has specific routing for dynamo cables and, while there is partial internal routing at the bike’s front end, the bars and stem are not integrated, which should allow for decent levels of adjustability. The bike exclusively comes with 1× gearing options, leaving Wilier open to widen the seat tube to act as a ‘small integrated mudguard’.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wilier has shirked the growing trend towards BSA standard bottom brackets, fitting the Adlar with a PF86 pressfit BB, which it says helped boost the tyre clearance.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Designed for adventure</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-6-647x970.jpg\" alt=\"Wilier Adlar gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-6-647x970.jpg 647w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-6-200x300.jpg 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-6-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-6-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-6-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-6-750x1124.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-6-1140x1709.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/Wilier_adlar_gravel-6-scaled.jpg 1708w\" /><figcaption>Alberto Squizzato</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Wilier is keen to highlight that this is a gravel bike designed for exploring and adventure, with an unusually high load capacity, geometry geared around good handling when fully laden, and multiple storage solutions. The key features are the panniers that mount directly via the thru-axles, a design that Wilier says helps distribute the added weight away from the frame for reduced structural stress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s also an extra down tube mount for a bottle or tool bag and a top tube mount, as well as specific mudguards that can be purchased separately.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To top off the storage options, Wilier collaborated with Miss Grape to provide a four-bag bikepacking kit, which is featured in two of the build options.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Wilier Adlar specs and pricing</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Wilier Adlar SRAM Rival XPLR AXS + bikepacking kit</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Frameset</strong>: Wilier Adlar<br /><strong>Groupset</strong>: SRAM Rival XPLR AXS<br /><strong>Wheelset</strong>: Miche Graff XL<br /><strong>Price</strong>: £4,644 / €5,400 / $5,878</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Wilier Adlar SRAM Rival XPLR AXS</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Frameset</strong>: Wilier Adlar<br /><strong>Groupset</strong>: SRAM Rival XPLR AXS<br /><strong>Wheelset</strong>: Miche Graff XL<br /><strong>Price</strong>: £4,128 / €4,800 / $5,225</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Wilier Adlar GRX 12spd + bikepacking kit</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Frameset</strong>: Wilier Adlar<br /><strong>Groupset</strong>: Shimano GRX 1×12<br /><strong>Wheelset</strong>: Miche Graff XL<br /><strong>Price</strong>: £3,956 / €4,600 / $5,007</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Wilier Adlar GRX 12spd</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Frameset</strong>: Wilier Adlar<br /><strong>Groupset</strong>: Shimano GRX 1×12<br /><strong>Wheelset</strong>: Miche Graff XL<br /><strong>Price</strong>: £3,440 / €4,000 / $4,354</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Wilier Adlar GRX 11spd</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Frameset</strong>: Wilier Adlar<br /><strong>Groupset</strong>: Shimano GRX 1×11<br /><strong>Wheelset</strong>: Miche Contact<br /><strong>Price</strong>: £3,182 / €3,700 / $4,028</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/wilier-adlar-gravel-bike\">The new Wilier Adlar adventure bike takes 35kg luggage max load and fits 52mm tyres</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Charlotte Head &#124; Tech Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"8d26940dd1e2d3a05e4bac8367fe2d0df3c16bfe0e6b674b696abfe287e53939","category":"Cycling"}